OL,3,C'Unacceptable' subscription traps
OL,4,Ccosting consumers #688m per year
OL,6,FConsumers face "worsening harm" from
OL,7,Fsubscription traps as the government's
OL,8,Fplans to fix the problem will fail,
OL,9,FCitizens Advice has warned.
OL,11,FMore than 13 million people have
OL,12,Faccidently taken out a subscription in
OL,13,Fthe last 12 months for services such
OL,14,Fas fitness apps, food delivery and
OL,15,Frepeat pet services.
OL,17,FResearch suggests that means that 26%
OL,18,Fof UK adults have footed a #688
OL,19,Fmillion bill over the past year just
OL,20,Fon unused subscriptions.
