OL,6,FCitizens Advice warned that the
OL,7,Ffailure to was not only a risk to
OL,8,Fconsumers, who could end up parting
OL,9,Fwith more money than they originally
OL,10,Fbargained for or could afford, but
OL,11,Falso harming businesses.
OL,13,FMore than half of people (54%) said
OL,14,Fthey had decided not to sign up for a
OL,15,Fsubscription due to concerns about how
OL,16,Fdifficult it would be to cancel.
OL,18,FThe charity found 74% of UK adults
OL,19,Fsupported a ban on automatic
OL,20,Fsubscription renewals where consumers
OL,21,Fhad not actively agreed to it.
