OL,3,C'Unacceptable' subscription traps
OL,4,Ccosting consumers #688m per year
OL,6,F"While the government has acknowledged
OL,7,Fsubscription traps are a problem that
OL,8,Fneed to be fixed, the plans laid out
OL,9,Fin the upcoming Consumer Bill risk
OL,10,Ffailing to fix them.
OL,12,F"We need to see the root cause of
OL,13,Fsubscription traps tackled head on.
OL,14,FConsumers should be offered a choice
OL,15,Fover whether their subscriptions auto-
OL,16,Frenew and whether they want to
OL,17,Fcontinue after a free trial."
